00:00:00:100000.Scene: A lecture room at the university.
00:00:00:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:00:100000.Dialogue: So, if any of you are considering going into experimental physics, my door is always open. Once again, I'm sorry the demonstration didn't quite work out, but now we know what happens when you accidentally spill Peach Snapple into a helium neon laser.

00:00:15:140000.Scene: A lecture room at the university.
00:00:15:140000.Speaker: Leonard

00:00:22:100000.Scene: A lecture room at the university.
00:00:22:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:22:100000.Dialogue: And now to tell you about the theoretical physics department is Dr. Sheldon Cooper.

00:00:32:010000.Scene: A lecture room at the university.
00:00:32:010000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:00:35:040000.Scene: A lecture room at the university.
00:00:35:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:35:040000.Dialogue: Excuse me. - Sheldon, we both agreed to do this.

00:00:37:180000.Scene: A lecture room at the university.
00:00:37:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:37:180000.Dialogue: - It's a waste of time. I might as well explain the laws of thermodynamics to a bunch of labradoodles.

00:00:46:040000.Scene: A lecture room at the university.
00:00:46:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:46:040000.Dialogue: If you don't do this, I won't take you to the comic book store.

00:00:58:210000.Scene: A lecture room at the university.
00:00:58:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:58:210000.Dialogue: Nice work with the laser, by the way.

00:01:03:230000.Scene: A lecture room at the university.
00:01:03:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:03:230000.Dialogue: Looking out at your fresh young faces, I remember when I too was deciding my academic future as a lowly graduate student. Of course, I was 14.

00:01:15:160000.Scene: A lecture room at the university.
00:01:15:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:15:160000.Dialogue: And I'd already achieved more than most of you could ever hope to, despite my 9:00 bedtime.

00:01:21:230000.Scene: A lecture room at the university.
00:01:21:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:21:230000.Dialogue: Now, there may be one or two of you in this room who has what it takes to succeed in theoretical physics. It's more likely that you'll spend your scientific careers teaching 5th graders how to make papier mache volcanoes with baking soda lava.

00:01:37:050000.Scene: A lecture room at the university.
00:01:37:050000.Speaker: Leonard

00:01:50:020000.Scene: A lecture room at the university.
00:01:50:020000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:01:54:080000.Scene: A lecture room at the university.
00:01:54:080000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:01:57:170000.Scene: A lecture room at the university.
00:01:57:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:57:170000.Dialogue: I weep for the future of science. Now if you'll excuse me, the latest issue of Batman is out.

00:02:03:120000.Scene: A lecture room at the university.
00:02:03:120000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:02:08:140000.Scene: A lecture room at the university.
00:02:08:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:08:140000.Dialogue: Laser demonstration's looking pretty good now, huh?

00:02:37:010000.Speaker: Raj
00:02:37:010000.Dialogue: I love this time of the year. The leaves are turning, there's a bracing chill in the air.

00:02:41:130000.Speaker: Howard
00:02:41:130000.Dialogue: Plus there's a whole new crop of female grad students about to put on just enough winter weight to make them needy and vulnerable.

00:02:50:150000.Speaker: Howard
00:02:50:150000.Dialogue: That's right, honey, have another calzone. Daddy can wait.

00:02:56:160000.Speaker: Raj
00:02:56:160000.Dialogue: Isn't there a university policy against dating graduate students?

00:02:59:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:59:130000.Dialogue: No, if you can talk to them, you can ask them out.

00:03:06:230000.Speaker: Leslie
00:03:06:230000.Dialogue: So, dumbass, I heard you made a grad student throw up last night.

00:03:11:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:11:080000.Dialogue: The truth can indeed be a finger down the throat of those unprepared to hear it.

00:03:16:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:16:210000.Dialogue: But why should I cater to second-rate minds?

00:03:19:100000.Speaker: Leslie
00:03:19:100000.Dialogue: Because first-rate minds call you dumbass?

00:03:24:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:24:160000.Dialogue: Oh, yeah? Well... you're a mean person.

00:03:29:230000.Speaker: Girl
00:03:29:230000.Dialogue: Excuse me, Dr. Cooper, I'm Ramona Nowitzki. I was at your talk last night. I think you're just brilliant.

00:03:41:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:41:200000.Dialogue: Howard Wolowitz, department of engineering, co-designer of the International Space Station's Liquid Waste Disposal System.

00:03:56:050000.Speaker: Ramona
00:03:56:050000.Dialogue: I've read everything you've published. I liked your paper on grand unification using string-network condensates and was wondering how you determined that 3-dimensional string-nets provided a unified picture of ferrnions and gauge bosons?

00:04:16:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:16:080000.Dialogue: The fact is I'm quite close to a breakthrough in showing how neutrinos emerge from a string-net condensate.

00:04:21:080000.Speaker: Ramona
00:04:21:080000.Dialogue: My God, that would change the way we view the entire physical universe.

00:04:27:130000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:27:130000.Dialogue: You know, the Pishkin-Wolowitz Liquid Waste Disposal System is turning a few heads as well.

00:04:41:220000.Speaker: Ramona
00:04:41:220000.Dialogue: I'd love to hear more about how you intend to add neutrinos. Could we get a cup of coffee sometime?

00:04:48:070000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:48:070000.Dialogue: I do. I love me a cup of joe.

00:04:51:050000.Speaker: Ramona
00:04:51:050000.Dialogue: It doesn't have to be coffee. How about dinner?

00:04:53:100000.Speaker: Ramona
00:04:53:100000.Dialogue: - Great. - I know a terrific Italian place.

00:04:54:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:54:210000.Dialogue: - I never eat in strange restaurants. One runs the risk of non-standard cutlery.

00:05:02:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:02:210000.Dialogue: Sheldon lives in fear of the three-tined fork.

00:05:06:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:06:230000.Dialogue: Three tines is not a fork. Three tines is a trident. Forks are for eating, tridents are for ruling the seven seas.

00:05:15:190000.Speaker: Ramona
00:05:15:190000.Dialogue: What if I brought food to your place?

00:05:17:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:17:180000.Dialogue: That would be acceptable. On Mondays, I eat Thai food. Mee krob and chicken sate with extra peanut sauce from Siam Palace.

00:05:24:200000.Speaker: Ramona
00:05:24:200000.Dialogue: You got it. I already have your address.

00:05:33:220000.Speaker: Howard
00:05:33:220000.Dialogue: Do you have any idea what just happened?

00:05:37:010000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:37:010000.Dialogue: Yes. Apparently I'm getting a free dinner.

00:05:45:020000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:05:45:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:45:020000.Dialogue: Oh, yeah, no, this thing's majorly out of order. - See? Sorry.

00:05:48:120000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:05:48:120000.Speaker: Ramona
00:05:48:120000.Dialogue: - That's okay. Guess I'm taking the stairs.

00:05:52:010000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:05:52:010000.Speaker: Penny

00:05:53:200000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:05:53:200000.Speaker: Ramona

00:05:57:070000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:05:57:070000.Speaker: Penny

00:06:00:140000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:06:00:140000.Speaker: Ramona

00:06:02:150000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:06:02:150000.Speaker: Penny

00:06:06:070000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:06:06:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:06:06:070000.Dialogue: Tall, thin, looks a little like a giant praying mantis?

00:06:12:150000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:06:12:150000.Speaker: Ramona

00:06:22:150000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:06:22:150000.Speaker: Penny

00:06:24:140000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:06:24:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:24:140000.Dialogue: - The kitchen's fine. - Hey, what are you doing?

00:06:28:090000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:06:28:090000.Speaker: Penny

00:06:33:050000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:06:33:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:33:050000.Dialogue: The viewing area's right over there.

00:06:37:220000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:06:37:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:37:220000.Dialogue: Sheldon, your girl... date... person... Ramona's here.

00:06:42:230000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:06:42:230000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:06:47:180000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:06:47:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:47:180000.Dialogue: Did you enjoy the humorous footnote where I illustrate mirror-symmetry by likening it to the Flash playing tennis with himself?

00:06:53:100000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:06:53:100000.Speaker: Ramona

00:06:55:220000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:06:55:220000.Speaker: Ramona
00:06:55:220000.Dialogue: But the idea that you might be able to incorporate gravity, I have to tell you, I found it physically exhilarating.

00:07:04:070000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:07:04:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:04:070000.Dialogue: My hypotheses tend to have that effect.

00:07:08:190000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:07:08:190000.Speaker: Ramona
00:07:08:190000.Dialogue: I'm sorry I didn't bring enough for your friends. I assumed we were going to be alone.

00:07:17:070000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:07:17:070000.Speaker: Leonard

00:07:19:000000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:07:19:000000.Speaker: Howard

00:07:22:120000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:07:22:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:22:120000.Dialogue: No, come on, now, we're going out.

00:07:24:090000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:07:24:090000.Speaker: Penny

00:07:27:120000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:07:27:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:27:120000.Dialogue: Let's go. Okay, you two. Have a nice... whatever this is.

00:07:39:090000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:07:39:090000.Speaker: Penny
00:07:39:090000.Dialogue: Okay, you guys, look, I know this is none of my business, but I just... I have to ask. What's Sheldon's deal?

00:07:49:110000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:07:49:110000.Speaker: Leonard

00:07:56:150000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:07:56:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:56:150000.Dialogue: Honestly, we've been operating under the assumption that he has no deal.

00:08:01:100000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:08:01:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:01:100000.Dialogue: Come on, everybody has a deal.

00:08:03:020000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:08:03:020000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:03:020000.Dialogue: Not Sheldon. Over the years, we've formulated many theories about how he might reproduce.

00:08:09:170000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:08:09:170000.Speaker: Howard

00:08:13:150000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:08:13:150000.Speaker: Penny

00:08:15:010000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:08:15:010000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:15:010000.Dialogue: I believe one day Sheldon will eat an enormous amount of Thai food and split into two Sheldons.

00:08:23:010000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:08:23:010000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:23:010000.Dialogue: On the other hand, I think Sheldon might be the larval form of his species, and someday he'll spin a cocoon and emerge two months later with moth wings and an exoskeleton.

00:08:32:180000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:08:32:180000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:32:180000.Dialogue: Okay, well, thanks for the nightmares.

00:08:37:010000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:08:37:010000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:37:010000.Dialogue: Hey, do you want to hang out with us?

00:08:39:200000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:08:39:200000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:39:200000.Dialogue: What are you guys gonna do?

00:08:43:180000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:08:43:180000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:43:180000.Dialogue: My mom's making a brisket tonight.

00:08:47:100000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:08:47:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:47:100000.Dialogue: The one with the little onions?

00:08:53:070000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:08:53:070000.Speaker: Penny

00:08:56:090000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:08:56:090000.Speaker: Penny

00:08:58:180000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:08:58:180000.Speaker: Howard

00:09:01:120000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:09:01:120000.Speaker: Raj

00:09:06:060000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:09:06:060000.Speaker: Raj

00:09:09:190000.Scene: The apartment building lobby. Ramona is waiting by the lift. Penny enters.
00:09:09:190000.Speaker: Leonard

00:09:20:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:20:090000.Dialogue: Are you experimenting with nutritional suppositories again?

00:09:28:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:28:140000.Dialogue: So... how'd it go with Ramona last night?

00:09:32:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:32:040000.Dialogue: Great. She's smart, insightful and she has a very unique way of, you know, revering me.

00:09:44:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:44:080000.Dialogue: Thank you. - Did anyone touch it?

00:09:46:120000.Speaker: Ramona
00:09:46:120000.Dialogue: - Gloves were worn by everyone involved. I was vigilant.

00:09:51:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:51:230000.Dialogue: Ramona pointed out that I've been wasting 20 minutes a day - standing on cafeteria lines.

00:09:54:180000.Speaker: Ramona
00:09:54:180000.Dialogue: - Time which would be better spent tackling the great physics problems of our day.

00:09:59:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:59:140000.Dialogue: You don't tackle the big issues. You fence with them. En garde. Riposte.

00:10:14:060000.Speaker: Leslie
00:10:14:060000.Dialogue: So I see you're organizing your papers for the Smithsonian Museum of Dumbassery.

00:10:20:150000.Speaker: Ramona
00:10:20:150000.Dialogue: There won't be any room until they get rid of the permanent Leslie Winkle exhibit.

00:10:28:220000.Speaker: Leslie
00:10:28:220000.Dialogue: I see you got a grad student to fight your battles for you. I'll let you keep your lunch money today.

00:10:34:160000.Speaker: Ramona
00:10:34:160000.Dialogue: Dr. Cooper is on the verge of a breakthrough. If you're going to stay, you'll have to be respectful and quiet.

00:10:54:090000.Speaker: Ramona
00:10:54:090000.Dialogue: Have you worked out the neutrino issue?

00:10:56:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:56:170000.Dialogue: Well, to paraphrase Mozart, all the subatomic particles are there. I just have to put them in the right order.

00:11:10:070000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:11:10:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:10:070000.Dialogue: Hey, guys, this package came for...

00:11:16:170000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:11:16:170000.Speaker: Ramona

00:11:18:070000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:11:18:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:18:070000.Dialogue: Yes, I'm close to a breakthrough. It tickles!

00:11:23:140000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:11:23:140000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:23:140000.Dialogue: Sorry. Holy crap on a cracker.

00:11:34:120000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:11:34:120000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:34:120000.Dialogue: You probably don't want to go in there.

00:11:36:230000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:11:36:230000.Speaker: Leonard

00:11:39:140000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:11:39:140000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:39:140000.Dialogue: The only way I could explain it would be in a therapist's office with dolls.

00:11:52:220000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:11:52:220000.Speaker: Leonard

00:11:55:190000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:11:55:190000.Speaker: Ramona

00:11:57:130000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:11:57:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:57:130000.Dialogue: Yeah, I can see that. Sheldon, Halo night, Koothrappali's. You coming?

00:12:02:180000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:12:02:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:02:180000.Dialogue: Yes, it's Halo night. Let me just dry my tootsies.

00:12:07:150000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:12:07:150000.Speaker: Ramona
00:12:07:150000.Dialogue: - You're not going to Halo night.

00:12:13:170000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:12:13:170000.Speaker: Ramona
00:12:13:170000.Dialogue: Didn't a great man once say, Science demands nothing less than the fervent and unconditional dedication of our entire lives?

00:12:21:080000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:12:21:080000.Speaker: Ramona
00:12:21:080000.Dialogue: - And who was that great man?

00:12:24:170000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:12:24:170000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:12:28:010000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:12:28:010000.Speaker: Leonard

00:12:30:210000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:12:30:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:30:210000.Dialogue: You heard her. How can I argue with me?

00:12:35:060000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:12:35:060000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:35:060000.Dialogue: Okay, well, once again, you guys have a good... whatever this is.

00:12:43:150000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:12:43:150000.Speaker: Ramona
00:12:43:150000.Dialogue: Dr. Cooper, I have to tell you your friends are holding you back.

00:12:47:090000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:12:47:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:47:090000.Dialogue: I prefer to think of it as I'm pulling them forward.

00:12:51:210000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:12:51:210000.Speaker: Ramona
00:12:51:210000.Dialogue: Halo night? A man with your intellectual gifts doesn't waste an evening playing video games.

00:12:57:150000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:12:57:150000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:13:00:040000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:13:00:040000.Speaker: Ramona
00:13:00:040000.Dialogue: Not if he wants a Nobel Prize.

00:13:02:170000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:13:02:170000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:13:07:020000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:13:07:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:07:020000.Dialogue: Does a man with my intellectual gifts play paintball on weekends?

00:13:10:210000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:13:10:210000.Speaker: Ramona

00:13:15:060000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:13:15:060000.Speaker: Ramona
00:13:15:060000.Dialogue: - Now shall we get back to work?

00:13:28:220000.Scene: The apartment. There is a knock on the door which then opens and Penny enters.
00:13:28:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:28:220000.Dialogue: And then, never ever watch it.

00:14:33:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:14:33:220000.Dialogue: Sheldon, honey, I've told you, it's a small apartment. You only have to knock one time.

00:14:38:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:38:070000.Dialogue: I don't have a lot of time. Ramona finally dozed off, and I need you to help me get rid of her.

00:14:48:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:48:030000.Dialogue: I don't know, but apparently I'm in some kind of relationship, and you seem to be an expert at ending them.

00:15:00:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:00:140000.Dialogue: I see man after man leaving this apartment never to return.

00:15:04:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:04:220000.Dialogue: Okay, first of all, it is not man after man.

00:15:22:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:22:110000.Dialogue: I told you, Penny, I don't have time for your nonsense. I have important things to do.

00:15:31:060000.Speaker: Ramona
00:15:31:060000.Dialogue: - I know what's going on here.

00:15:35:210000.Speaker: Ramona
00:15:35:210000.Dialogue: You're in love with Dr. Cooper.

00:15:42:030000.Speaker: Ramona
00:15:42:030000.Dialogue: Don't try to deny it. He's a remarkable man, but you have to let him go.

00:15:50:230000.Speaker: Ramona
00:15:50:230000.Dialogue: I know it's hard, but he's a gift to the whole world, and we can't be selfish.

00:15:55:120000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:55:120000.Dialogue: Yeah, he's a gift all right.

00:16:35:180000.Dialogue: So we can communicate through the wall.

00:16:39:080000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:16:39:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:39:080000.Dialogue: We are communicating through the wall.

00:16:42:120000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:16:42:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:42:120000.Dialogue: Yes, but the communication is not encrypted.

00:16:46:080000.Speaker: Leonard

00:16:48:060000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:16:48:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:48:060000.Dialogue: It's very simple. This is A... This is B... - This is C.

00:16:52:140000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:16:52:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:52:140000.Dialogue: - I'm not going to learn Morse code at 3:00 in the morning!

00:16:56:040000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:16:56:040000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:16:58:200000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:16:58:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:58:200000.Dialogue: Don't come in here, don't come in here...

00:17:06:100000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:17:06:100000.Speaker: Leonard

00:17:07:160000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:17:07:160000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:17:09:160000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:17:09:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:09:160000.Dialogue: I know. When is she going home?

00:17:11:150000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:17:11:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:11:150000.Dialogue: Never. That's the problem. - I need your help.

00:17:14:070000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:17:14:070000.Speaker: Leonard

00:17:17:060000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:17:17:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:17:060000.Dialogue: I'm invoking the Skynet clause of our friendship agreement.

00:17:21:030000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:17:21:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:21:030000.Dialogue: That only applies if you need me to help you destroy an artificial intelligence you've created that's taking over the Earth.

00:17:27:160000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:17:27:160000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:17:31:040000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:17:31:040000.Speaker: Leonard

00:17:32:170000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:17:32:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:32:170000.Dialogue: All right. I'm invoking our Body Snatchers clause.

00:17:38:130000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:17:38:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:38:130000.Dialogue: The Body Snatchers clause requires me to help you destroy someone we know who's been replaced with an alien pod.

00:17:44:030000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:17:44:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:44:030000.Dialogue: She's in the living room. Go. I'll wait here.

00:17:47:100000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:17:47:100000.Speaker: Ramona
00:17:47:100000.Dialogue: Sheldon, what are you doing out of bed?

00:17:49:120000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:17:49:120000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:17:54:030000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:17:54:030000.Speaker: Ramona
00:17:54:030000.Dialogue: You know you need your sleep in order for your cognitive processing to perform at optimum levels. Now come on.

00:17:59:010000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:17:59:010000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:18:01:030000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:18:01:030000.Speaker: Leonard

00:18:04:060000.Scene: Leonard’s bedroom. He is asleep. There is a tapping on the wall. He wakes up.
00:18:04:060000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:18:07:080000.Scene: The living room. Sheldon is surrounded by whiteboards.
00:18:07:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:07:080000.Dialogue: I've got it! I finally reconciled the black hole information paradox with my theory of string-network condensates!

00:18:14:150000.Scene: The living room. Sheldon is surrounded by whiteboards.
00:18:14:150000.Speaker: Ramona

00:18:17:120000.Scene: The living room. Sheldon is surrounded by whiteboards.
00:18:17:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:17:120000.Dialogue: I could not have done it without you.

00:18:19:080000.Scene: The living room. Sheldon is surrounded by whiteboards.
00:18:19:080000.Speaker: Ramona
00:18:19:080000.Dialogue: Please, I just offered a little encouragement.

00:18:21:170000.Scene: The living room. Sheldon is surrounded by whiteboards.
00:18:21:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:21:170000.Dialogue: It was a lot more than that. You helped me work out the masses of all the fermions and you pumiced my hammer toe.

00:18:29:040000.Scene: The living room. Sheldon is surrounded by whiteboards.
00:18:29:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:29:040000.Dialogue: How can I ever repay you?

00:18:31:090000.Scene: The living room. Sheldon is surrounded by whiteboards.
00:18:31:090000.Speaker: Ramona
00:18:31:090000.Dialogue: Would you consider naming it the Cooper-Nowitzki Theorem?

00:18:34:070000.Scene: The living room. Sheldon is surrounded by whiteboards.
00:18:34:070000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:18:37:160000.Scene: The living room. Sheldon is surrounded by whiteboards.
00:18:37:160000.Speaker: Ramona

00:18:39:120000.Scene: The living room. Sheldon is surrounded by whiteboards.
00:18:39:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:39:120000.Dialogue: You want me to share credit? Get out!

00:18:56:210000.Scene: The cafeteria. A red haired girl approaches the table.
00:18:56:210000.Speaker: Girl

00:18:59:020000.Scene: The cafeteria. A red haired girl approaches the table.
00:18:59:020000.Speaker: Girl
00:18:59:020000.Dialogue: I'm Kathy O'Brien. I just finished reading your paper reconciling the black hole information paradox with your theory of string-network condensates, and it just took my breath away.

00:19:09:190000.Scene: The cafeteria. A red haired girl approaches the table.
00:19:09:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:09:190000.Dialogue: Maybe when I publish it, I'll include an inhaler.

00:19:16:030000.Scene: The cafeteria. A red haired girl approaches the table.
00:19:16:030000.Speaker: Kathy
00:19:16:030000.Dialogue: Would you possibly have any time for me to pick your brain?

00:19:19:220000.Scene: The cafeteria. A red haired girl approaches the table.
00:19:19:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:19:220000.Dialogue: Let's see. Today's Thursday. Thursday nights, I eat pizza from Giacomo's. Sausage, mushrooms, light olives.

00:19:25:070000.Scene: The cafeteria. A red haired girl approaches the table.
00:19:25:070000.Speaker: Kathy
00:19:25:070000.Dialogue: Great. I'll bring it to your place. I have the address.

00:19:32:070000.Scene: The cafeteria. A red haired girl approaches the table.
00:19:32:070000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:19:35:200000.Scene: The cafeteria. A red haired girl approaches the table.
00:19:35:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:35:200000.Dialogue: Sheldon, do you see what just happened here?

00:19:38:110000.Scene: The cafeteria. A red haired girl approaches the table.
00:19:38:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:38:110000.Dialogue: Yes, I'm getting a free pizza.
